##Create multiple buttons

To generate multiple alerts you can use the generic @mixin <%= link_to 'mars-build-components','documentation/builders/mars-build-components' %>, visit the page on the builder to better understand how it works and arguments.

<% example_tabs do %>
~~~scss
%button {
  @include log('üì¶ extend %button');
  @include mars-button;
}

@include mars-build-components(
  $prefix: '.btn',
  $extend: '%button',
  $elements: $mars-buttons
);
~~~

~~~css
.btn-primary, .btn-default {
  /* ///////// üì¶ extend %button */
  /* ///////// üõ∏ mars-button */
  padding: 0.4em 1em;
  cursor: pointer;
  border: 1px solid;
  border-radius: 5px;
  transition: color .2s ease-out, background-color .2s ease-out; }

/* ///////// ‚òÑÔ∏è mars-build-components .btn */
.btn-primary {
  color: #fff;
  background-color: #dc3545; }
  .btn-primary:active, .btn-primary:focus, .btn-primary:hover, .btn-primary.is-active {
    background-color: #bd2130; }

.btn-default {
  color: #fff;
  background-color: #495057; }
  .btn-default:active, .btn-default:focus, .btn-default:hover, .btn-default.is-active {
