The `$mars-buttons` contains the variations written on a map and its name is generated by adding the prefix that we pass to the mixin.



~~~scss
//we store the different selectors in a variable
$mars-button-active: '&:active, &:focus, &:hover, &.is-active' !default;

$mars-buttons:(
  '-primary': (
    color: $white,
    background-color: $primary,
    $mars-button-active: (
      background-color: darken($primary, 10%)
    )
  ),
  '-default':(
    color: $white,
    background-color: $gray-700,
    $mars-button-active: (
      background-color: darken($gray-700, 10%)
    )
  )
) !default;
~~~

##create multiple variations

If we would like, for example, to have other buttons with another size using the same elements, we could create a new `@extend`, in this example we will add all at once to be able to see the resulting css

<% example_tabs do %>

~~~scss
%button {
  @include log('üì¶ extend %button');
  @include mars-button;
}

@include mars-build-components(
  $prefix: '.btn',
  $extend: '%button',
  $elements: $mars-buttons
);

%button-sm {
  @include log('üì¶ extend %button-sm');
  @extend %button;
  font-size: $font-size-small;
}

@include mars-build-components(
  $prefix: '.btn-sm',
  $extend: '%button-sm',
  $elements: $mars-buttons
);
~~~

